 "id": "yelvar",
 "name": "Yelvar — Western Valley",
 "world": "Yelvar",
 "description": "Closed canopy with one clearing — the only place in the valley with real sightlines. A trail runs through it south to north. Whoever holds the clearing holds the valley; whoever leaves it first answers for why.",
 "ambientRegister": "Oppressive green under closed canopy. Insect noise, amplified footfalls, near-silence between clashes.",
 "designRationale": "The forest is the map: it slows movement and kills vision everywhere except the clearing, so the clearing is the designed collision point. Three approaches with different risk profiles converge on it. The reposition order targets terrain you can already see (the north trail) — the dilemma is legible from deployment.",
